If you can log in but see no data, ensure your **Firestore Rules** are set correctly. In the Firebase Console under **Firestore > Rules**, use this to allow you to read/write your own data:

```javascript
rules_version = '2';
service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {
    match /users/{userId}/{document=**} {
      allow read, write: if request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == userId;
    }
  }
}
```

This setup ensures that even if another admin uses the app, they can **only** see their own borrowers, and your data remains private and secure.

